# Map Safety Notifier - Project Standards

## Project Overview

Community safety map app (Brazilian Portuguese) for reporting urban issues (flood, pothole, robbery, etc.) on an interactive map. Users can report, vote, and track persistence of unresolved problems.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite (SWC)
- **UI**: shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) + Tailwind CSS 3
- **Maps**: Leaflet + react-leaflet (CARTO dark tiles)
- **State**: TanStack React Query v5 (local/mock data por enquanto)
- **Routing**: React Router DOM v6
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Charts**: Recharts
- **Dates**: date-fns (ptBR locale)

> **Nota**: Projeto 100% front-end por enquanto. Dados são mock/local. Backend (Supabase) será integrado futuramente.

## Architecture

```
src/
  pages/          → Route-level components
  components/     → Feature components
  components/ui/  → shadcn/ui primitives (do NOT modify manually)
  hooks/          → Custom React hooks (dados mock/local)
  controllers/    → Business logic (mock data por enquanto)
  lib/            → Utility functions
  types/          → Shared TypeScript types
```

## Code Style

- Functional components only, no classes
- Named exports for all components and hooks
- Path alias: `@/` maps to `src/`
- Descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs: `isLoading`, `hasError`, `canSubmit`
- File naming: PascalCase for components (`PinDetails.tsx`), camelCase for utilities (`helpers.ts`)
- Locale: Brazilian Portuguese for all user-facing text

## Key Conventions

- Never modify files inside `src/components/ui/` directly — use shadcn CLI
- Keep page components thin: delegate logic to hooks and controllers
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Default map center: Franco da Rocha (-23.3343, -46.6953)
- Map bounds: Franco da Rocha, Caieiras, Mairiporã, Francisco Morato (SW: -23.45,-46.82 / NE: -23.18,-46.48)
- Pin types: `flood`, `pothole`, `passable`, `robbery`
